-- Turkey’s Kasimpasaspor Says Signs Swedish Goalkeeper Isaksson
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-07-09T12:36:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-09/turkey-s-kasimpasaspor-says-signs-swedish-goalkeeper-isaksson.html
Kasimpasaspor, an Istanbul-based
soccer team, said it signed 31-year-old Swedish national team
goalkeeper Andreas Isaksson to a three-year deal.  Isaksson will join the team in training at a one-month
training camp that begins in the Netherlands today, Kasimpasa
Spor Kulubu said in a  statement  on its website. It didn’t give
financial terms of the deal.  Isaksson previously played for  PSV Eindhoven  in the
Netherlands and between 1999 and 2001 for Juventus in  Italy ,
according to data compiled by Bloomberg. He has 139 appearances
for the Swedish national team, according to Kasimpasaspor’s
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
